&lt;h2&gt;Comparative Study of Regularization Techniques in Logistic Regression&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img src="leukemia-2.jpg" alt="Leukemia Study" width="100%" style="border-radius: 10px;"&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;Project Overview&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
  The primary objective of this project is to analyze a leukemia gene expression dataset using various penalized regression methods. 
  The analysis applies &lt;strong&gt;Lasso, Ridge, and Elastic Net&lt;/strong&gt; to identify the most significant genes associated with leukemia and to develop robust logistic regression models for classifying leukemia subtypes.
&lt;/p&gt;

