&lt;h2&gt;Estimation of Lending Phase & Interest Rate in Microfinance&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;img src="microfinance.jpg" alt="Interest Rate Study" width="100%" style="border-radius: 10px;"&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;Project Overview&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
  The study calculates the &lt;strong&gt;optimal interest rate&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;lending phase duration&lt;/strong&gt; to ensure financial sustainability and prevent strategic borrower defaults.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
  A low interest rate results in microfinance institutions running at a loss, while a high interest rate leads to borrower defaults. This research helps strike the perfect balance.
&lt;/p&gt;

